XIV. TO POSTUMUS

Elzezc fugaces, Postume, Postume

Y Postumus, the fleeting years Pass swiftly. N either prayers nor tears Can smooth the lines by age imprest Or Death's advancing step arrest, —

Not if three hundred bulls a day

You should to tearless Pluto slay, Whose Stygiam waters' circling chain The Giants strive to break in vain, -

Waters that all of mortal birth

Must cross who eat the fruits of Earth, Whether they bask in wealth‚ or toil To win scant fare from stubborn soil.
